    How do I get my title deeds after I pay off my mortgage?
    If you'd like a copy of your deeds, you can do this by contacting the Land Registry. If your property is not registered with the Land Registry, you may have paper title deeds instead. If you don't have your original title deeds, they may be stored with your mortgage provider.
